Findings (Fix Before Launch)

Hardcoded production MongoDB credentials in app startup
Evidence: app.js:20
Risk: Secret leakage, unauthorized database access, accidental writes to production from local/dev.
Missing part:
Remove fallback URI with credentials.
Require MONGO_URL from environment and fail fast if missing.
Weak JWT fallback secret shared in both auth generation and verification
Evidence: auth.controller.js:6, auth.middleware.js:3
Risk: Anyone who knows default string can forge valid tokens.
Missing part:
Remove fallback secret.
Enforce JWT_SECRET presence at startup.
Rotate secret for production immediately if this app has been used publicly.
Launch path has no top-level startup error boundary
Evidence: app.js:53, app.js:40, app.js:41
Risk: Rejected promise during startup (for example seed failure) can crash process without clean log/exit strategy.
Missing part:
Wrap startup call in catch and exit with clear message.
Add process-level handlers for unhandledRejection and uncaughtException with structured logging.
Unauthenticated write/read endpoints for core business data
Evidence:
Orders write endpoints: order.routes.js:33, order.routes.js:34, order.routes.js:35, order.routes.js:36
Public location mutation endpoint: location.routes.js:12, location.routes.js:13
Risk: Anonymous users can create/update/delete orders and locations.
Missing part:
Add auth middleware and role guard to all mutating endpoints.
Keep only explicitly public endpoints unauthenticated (for example tracking).
High Findings

Null dereference crash possibility when updating user
Evidence: user.controller.js:173, user.controller.js:174
Risk: If id is valid format but not found, user is null, then property assignment throws and returns 500.
Missing part:
Check existence after findById.
Return 404 for not found.
Inconsistent API prefixing can cause integration failures after deployment
Evidence: app.js:31, app.js:32, order.routes.js:37, driver.routes.js:14
Risk: Mixed endpoints with and without /api lead to client confusion and broken routing in gateways/reverse proxies.
Missing part:
Standardize mount strategy, for example app.use("/api", ...routes).
Keep route files relative, without hardcoded /api in some endpoints only.
JWT parsing is fragile and returns wrong status code for malformed header formats
Evidence: auth.middleware.js:7, auth.middleware.js:10, auth.middleware.js:15
Risk: Authorization header without Bearer token can throw and be treated as invalid token with 400 instead of 401.
Missing part:
Validate Authorization format strictly: Bearer <token>.
Return 401 for all auth failures.
Medium Findings

Delete and get user endpoints do not handle not-found explicitly
Evidence: user.controller.js:155, user.controller.js:164, user.controller.js:165
Risk: Returns success or null body where 404 is expected, causing frontend state bugs.
Missing part:
Return 404 when findById/findByIdAndDelete returns null.
Amount validation rejects zero via truthy check
Evidence: collection.controller.js:17, payment.controller.js:17
Risk: Logic bug if zero-amount records are ever valid (or unclear behavior).
Missing part:
Validate with amount == null and explicit numeric constraints.
No centralized error middleware in Express
Evidence: app.js
Risk: Inconsistent error response shape, duplicated try/catch, harder debugging.
Missing part:
Add global error handler and optional async wrapper helper.
